<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_Restaurant_Funds" s="142621">
  <T n="category">143449<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_DineOut--></T>
  <T n="name">0xD229FC71<!--String: "Restaurants - Funds"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_funds_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:584f02e1cf8fdf71</T>
      <T n="text">0x831E9BBB<!--String: "As a restaurant owner, your restaurant's funds are tracked separately from your normal household funds. Each restaurant that you own has its own separate funds that are used to cover the restaurant's expenses. When you visit your restaurant, you can simultaneously view your restaurant's funds in the Owned Businesses panel in the bottom right corner, along with your household's funds in the bottom left corner."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_funds_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:584f02e1cf8fdf72</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial_controller\restaurant_funds_2_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:dafc2f2d1818c09d</T>
      <T n="text">0x12003351<!--String: "Every action taken as an owner while at your restaurant uses money from your business' funds. This includes building on the restaurant lot, placing objects, paying your employees, purchasing advertising, and more. When you enter Build Mode, the money shown in the bottom left corner will switch to display your restaurant funds that you're building with. Finally, any money you earn from your restaurant's sales will be deposited into your restaurant funds."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_funds_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:584f02e1cf8fdf73</T>
      <T n="text">0x262BD1ED<!--String: "There's a chance that your restaurant can go into debt if you don't have enough money to pay your employees, or if you purchase advertising while low on funds. If your restaurant doesn't have enough money to pay its debts, you won't be allowed to reopen your restaurant until those debts have been cleared. Transfer money from your household to your restaurant to cover your debts."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_funds_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:584f02e1cf8fdf74</T>
      <T n="text">0xC60B86C3<!--String: "At any time you can use the Venue Funds Transfer button near your household's Simoleons in the bottom left corner to move money between your household and any of the restaurants that you own. Within this panel you can select the account you're transferring from and to, and enter the amount of money you want to transfer. Try transferring funds when you need more money to pay your business' expenses, or to send the profits from your business back to your household."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial\restaurant_funds_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:584f02e1cf8fdf75</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InGP03\UI\Tutorial_controller\restaurant_funds_5_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a79f71480064eea8</T>
      <T n="text">0xE8F598A1<!--String: "You can click on the "View Shift Summary/Last Finances" button on the Owned Businesses panel to get a detailed breakdown of your profits and expenses. Use this information to make strategic decisions about your restaurant to help maximize profits."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
</I>